16struct nouveau_bo {
17 struct ttm_buffer_object bo;
18 struct ttm_placement placement;
19 u32 valid_domains;
20 struct ttm_place placements[3];
21 struct ttm_place busy_placements[3];
22 bool force_coherent;
23 struct ttm_bo_kmap_obj kmap;
24 struct list_head head;
25
26 /* protected by ttm_bo_reserve() */
27 struct drm_file *reserved_by;
28 struct list_head entry;
29 int pbbo_index;
30 bool validate_mapped;
31
32 struct list_head vma_list;
33 unsigned page_shift;
34
35 u32 tile_mode;
36 u32 tile_flags;
37 struct nouveau_drm_tile *tile;
38
39 /* Only valid if allocated via nouveau_gem_new() and iff you hold a
40 * gem reference to it! For debugging, use gem.filp != NULL to test
41 * whether it is valid. */
42 struct drm_gem_object gem;
43
44 /* protect by the ttm reservation lock */
45 int pin_refcnt;
46
47 struct ttm_bo_kmap_obj dma_buf_vmap;
48};
49
50static inline struct nouveau_bo *
51nouveau_bo(struct ttm_buffer_object *bo)
52{
53 return container_of(bo, struct nouveau_bo, bo);
54}
55
56static inline int
57nouveau_bo_ref(struct nouveau_bo *ref, struct nouveau_bo **pnvbo)
58{
59 struct nouveau_bo *prev;
60
61 if (!pnvbo)
62 return -EINVAL;
63 prev = *pnvbo;
64
65 *pnvbo = ref ? nouveau_bo(ttm_bo_reference(&ref->bo)) : NULL;
66 if (prev) {
67 struct ttm_buffer_object *bo = &prev->bo;
68
69 ttm_bo_unref(&bo);
70 }
71
72 return 0;
73}

108/* TODO: submit equivalent to TTM generic API upstream? */
109static inline void __iomem *
110nvbo_kmap_obj_iovirtual(struct nouveau_bo *nvbo)
111{
112 bool is_iomem;
113 void __iomem *ioptr = (void __force __iomem *)ttm_kmap_obj_virtual(
114 &nvbo->kmap, &is_iomem);
115 WARN_ON_ONCE(ioptr && !is_iomem);
116 return ioptr;
117}
